"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"This paper presents an analytical study of the language features of English advertisements at lexical, syntactic and discourse levels. In order to conduct a data-driven study, the author builds a corpus of 60 English advertisements. It is hoped that through the detailed survey of three types of advertisements: namely, daily consumer goods ads, technical equipment ads, service ads, similarities and differences in advertising language features can be summarized and possible reasons will be given in the light of the meaning, and function of language.\",\"timestamp\":1638955645,\"title\":\"In order to conduct a data-driven study\"},\"digest\":\"QmrV3n8-iiAT-g7mVUi5UXTOxcDIR0EIIJLWYPV-4q4\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xA797Ad68D67d854eb79E816E5Eb8b2fc6244692B\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"FStipDXzqblY4w2uLGHjc-uPtNOheHBmoRcQ36Gdy58\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Q3Ru0Is-i5Kcb-C6-WPqSClTVR4KAVxjVrDb5uiZAMo\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"yRFPcoWjBCSd_sS1Q1BbA4jqvAbKizsQ5i1EuzsJ0C2vdvv26taLzmZB8XZ4knqSZokjIFDQc-vHRVdxCGPt5A\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x5ed77d9f45bce1621774930734a3e2ba604dc9c1cce5f9b4042539a6237619884130a1f78ba83b1a1193a4b686efea35207d6c04a27a910c243f611f95a6e39f1c\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"FStipDXzqblY4w2uLGHjc-uPtNOheHBmoRcQ36Gdy58\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"Q3Ru0Is-i5Kcb-C6-WPqSClTVR4KAVxjVrDb5uiZAMo\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"QmrV3n8-iiAT-g7mVUi5UXTOxcDIR0EIIJLWYPV-4q4\"}"